<p>The RDF reflects the probability density between two types of atoms and can reflect the aggregation characteristics of ions in the system. The RDF of β particles is evaluated as follows [
 <xref rid="B33-ijms-20-03997" ref-type="bibr">33</xref>]: 
 <disp-formula id="FD2-ijms-20-03997">
  <label>(2)</label>
  <math id="mm3">
   <mrow>
    <mrow>
     <msub>
      <mi mathvariant="normal">g</mi>
      <mrow>
       <mi>α</mi>
       <mi>β</mi>
      </mrow>
     </msub>
     <mrow>
      <mo>(</mo>
      <mi>r</mi>
      <mo>)</mo>
     </mrow>
     <mo>=</mo>
     <msub>
      <mi>n</mi>
      <mi>β</mi>
     </msub>
     <mo>/</mo>
     <mn>4</mn>
     <mi>π</mi>
     <msub>
      <mi>ρ</mi>
      <mi>β</mi>
     </msub>
     <msup>
      <mi>r</mi>
      <mn>2</mn>
     </msup>
     <mi mathvariant="normal">d</mi>
     <mi>r</mi>
    </mrow>
   </mrow>
  </math>
 </disp-formula> where g
 <italic>
  <sub>αβ</sub>
 </italic>(
 <italic>r</italic>) is the radial distribution of 
 <italic>β</italic>, 
 <italic>n
  <sub>β</sub>
 </italic> is the number of 
 <italic>β</italic> with a radius of 
 <italic>r</italic> → 
 <italic>r</italic> + d
 <italic>r</italic>, 
 <italic>ρ
  <sub>β</sub>
 </italic> is the number density of 
 <italic>β</italic>, and 
 <italic>r</italic> is the distance between 
 <italic>α</italic> and 
 <italic>β</italic>.
</p>
